Asked Copilot to rewrite this with the `race` idea:

> instead of looping over each processPromise in the order of codesignTasks, do a loop in which it waits for the first promise to complete, then print the banner and pipe the output, and goes back to the start of the loop excluding that task

Came up with this:

```ts
// Wait for processes to finish and stream their output
const tasks = [...codesignTasks];
while (tasks.length > 0) {
	// Wait for the first process to complete
	const completedIndex = await Promise.race(tasks.map((task, index) => 
		task.processPromise.then(() => index)));
	
	// Get the completed task
	const { banner, processPromise } = tasks[completedIndex];
	
	// Print banner and pipe output
	printBanner(banner);
	await processPromise.pipe(process.stdout);
	
	// Remove the completed task
	tasks.splice(completedIndex, 1);
}
```

